# Financial Risk Operational Insurance Offset Amount

## identifier
de8177

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of insurance offset amount, as determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards.

Insurance offset represents that amount of insurance that will cover potential operational risk losses and which is deemed an appropriate operational risk mitigation method.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.Operational.InsuranceOffset.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=instant
